1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,100
♪I love the clarity in your eyes♪

2
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:13,860
♪Like a shooting star across my world♪

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,580
♪Repeating the goodbye we never said♪

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,540
♪Through sleepless nights♪

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,100
♪I miss the way you looked at me♪

6
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:30,260
♪Like photos freezing that summer bit by bit♪

7
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:35,380
♪By the shore with warm winds, maybe we'll meet again♪

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:41,460
[Fall in Love Again]

9
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:43,980
[Episode 16]

10
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:45,320
Xiwen,

11
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,840
you said the accident wasn't an accident.

12
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:48,960
Did you find something?

13
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:53,320
There's something off about him.

14
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,120
Isn't he the prop guy?

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:00,040
What about him?

16
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:02,080
He installed the balcony railing.

17
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:03,760
He swore up and down

18
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:05,560
that everything was checked.

19
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:07,240
But the moment I halted production

20
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,640
and ordered a full safety review,

21
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,560
he claimed his mom was sick and bailed.

22
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:15,360
Maybe his mom really is sick.

23
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:16,160
Nonsense.

24
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:17,400
I checked.

25
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,000
This guy's mom

26
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,720
was at Nanhu Plaza yesterday,

27
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:22,840
competing in the city seniors' dance contest.

28
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,560
She's healthier than I am.

29
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:29,640
That lowlife.

30
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,280
I checked. No one's around.

31
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,760
Didn't I tell you to leave here?

32
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,360
I'd love to.

33
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,840
But I've got bills to pay.

34
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:47,960
The money you gave me

35
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,440
isn't enough.

36
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,360
I wired you two payments,

37
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,960
two hundred grand in total. That's not enough?

38
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,760
Can you at least play by the rules?

39
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,040
I know the rules.

40
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,040
Normally, once I take your money,

41
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,480
we're square.

42
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,080
But things have changed.

43
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,440
Mr. Song's already suspicious.

44
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,320
They're looking into it.

45
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:12,560
Fine.

46
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,360
I'll wire the money.

47
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,520
But remember what you said today.

48
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,040
If this blows up,

49
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,040
keep my name out of it.

50
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:20,640
Another five hundred thousand.

51
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,120
If anything happens,

52
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,240
I'll take the fall.

53
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,520
Another five hundred thousand?

54
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,240
You're asking for a lot!

55
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,040
Director Qi,

56
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,840
I'm doing this for your sake.

57
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,360
If I asked for less,

58
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,440
would you really sleep easy?

59
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,640
You're real generous, huh?

60
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:39,280
You flatter me.

61
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:43,440
I'll send the money now.

62
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,880
Just don't forget what you promised today.

63
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:46,840
Relax.

64
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:49,500
[Transfer Complete: 500,000]

65
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,360
Mr. Song, Ms. Chu,

66
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:05,120
our project's been on hold for two days now.

67
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,320
There's a lot of talk going around the crew.

68
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,360
Some say there's an issue with the IP.

69
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,640
Others say we've run out of funding,

70
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,280
and that's why production stopped.

71
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,840
That's not even the worst of it.

72
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,240
I've even heard rumors

73
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,640
that Mr. Song

74
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:23,240
pulled his investment

75
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,720
after being rejected by Ms. Chu.

76
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,680
Why is everyone staring at me?

77
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,880
I'm just repeating what's being said.

78
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,360
No need to be awkward.

79
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,880
In our line of work,

80
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,880
a bit of gossip comes with the job.

81
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:51,280
Everyone knows what you're really after.

82
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:56,240
Besides, if I were truly pursuing Ms. Chu,

83
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:57,760
I wouldn't

84
00:03:57,760 --> 00:04:00,560
give up over a single rejection.

85
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,240
Ms. Chu.

86
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,240
Since everyone's worried about the shutdown,

87
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,040
why don't you say a few words

88
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,640
to clear things up?

89
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,520
Alright.

90
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,160
I can say this with full confidence:

91
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:23,880
our funding is solid.

92
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,440
The IP rights are fully under our control.

93
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,480
As for the rumor that

94
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,040
Mr. Song withdrew after I rejected him,

95
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,320
that's completely false.

96
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:36,560
Please let the entire crew know,

97
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,640
production will resume within three days.

98
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:43,280
Before this meeting, I informed finance

99
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,640
to release all remaining funds

100
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,040
in advance,

101
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,720
so everyone can rest easy.

102
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,440
Hearing that from Ms. Chu

103
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,640
puts me at ease.

104
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:52,640
Good.

105
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,160
Excuse me.

106
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:58,360
Hello?

107
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,240
Hang on a second.

108
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:02,960
Please go on.

109
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,960
Any other questions today?

110
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,840
- No. - All good.

111
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,040
Alright, that's it for today.

112
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,480
Ai, come with me.

113
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,280
- Okay. - Let's go.

114
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,920
I'm not sure either. I'll be more careful next time.

115
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,280
Let's not let this happen again.

116
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:32,840
Ms. Qian.

117
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:33,640
Ms. Qian.

118
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:34,720
What's up?

119
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,960
I've got two theater tickets.

120
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,160
Wanna catch a play tonight?

121
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,160
Bad timing.

122
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,840
I've got a yoga session scheduled today.

123
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,040
Maybe another time.

124
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,920
[Time moves on. We never drift apart.]
Since you're busy tonight,

125
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,880
I've got two tickets for tomorrow.

126
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,840
Wanna go see it tomorrow?

127
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,160
Tomorrow?

128
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,320
Tomorrow won't work either.

129
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,640
I've got a riding lesson.

130
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,080
Well...

131
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:05,240
Then let's stay in touch.

132
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,960
You scared me.

133
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:09,360
I thought you'd pull out two more tickets.

134
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:09,960
Nope, that's it.

135
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,640
Well,

136
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,440
let's do it another day.

137
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,800
Let's message more, Ms. Qian.

138
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,720
You've gotta reply.

139
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:19,040
If you don't, how am I supposed to ask you out?

140
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,080
That's cold.

141
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:23,840
Speak plainly.

142
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:26,840
Feels like we're drifting.

143
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:30,360
You went way too hard just now.

144
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:32,720
Serves you right.

145
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,840
You almost embarrassed me back there.

146
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:37,440
Try that again and I'll step on your foot.

147
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,520
Since when were you this cold? I never noticed.

148
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,280
Better late than never. Scared now?

149
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:52,840
No matter how cold you are, I can melt you.

150
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:02,260
♪As we draw closer...♪

151
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,760
He Zheng, let's go!

152
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:11,840
Thanks.

153
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,240
About that scene just now,

154
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,840
that worked fine, right?

155
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,120
Yeah, it's good.

156
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,080
Jiayang,

157
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,320
what's up?

158
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,120
Nothing.

159
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:22,800
I'll leave you two to it.

160
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,080
This is all your fault.

161
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:28,880
We got caught.

162
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,840
So what?

163
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,280
If he dares say a word, he's done.

164
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,040
Okay, Mr. Wang.

165
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,840
No problem. Looking forward to working together.

166
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:40,960
Alright, let's leave it at that.

167
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,780
[Song Xiwen]

168
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,000
Hello?

169
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,840
Xi, have you left yet?

170
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,040
Not yet. I'm still at the office.

171
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,480
I'm meeting an investor later.

172
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,040
Come with me.

173
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:18,840
Okay.

174
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,840
I don't want you meeting Song Xiwen.

175
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,240
Be good. It's just work.

176
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,030
Then give me a kiss.

177
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,880
Everything set?

178
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:50,320
All set.

179
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,640
Alright, let's go.

180
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,680
The way Song Xiwen looked at me back then...

181
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,720
That was straight-up provocation.

182
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,080
Do you think he noticed something?

183
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,360
And sent my Chu away on purpose?

184
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,640
So when did you two start?

185
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:19,800
Get lost.

186
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:21,440
Answer the question.

187
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,840
It's not like you stole his girlfriend.

188
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,880
So what are you scared of?

189
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:28,840
But still...

190
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,520
he's the big boss of our company now.

191
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,680
If you piss him off,

192
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,440
it won't end well for you.

193
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,040
You think I'm afraid of him?

194
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,560
That's ridiculous.

195
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,480
Forget whether you're scared or not.

196
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:45,240
Just tell me, when did it start?

197
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:45,840
Get lost.

198
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:48,560
I...

199
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,640
What are you up to, Qian?

200
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,040
Simp.

201
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:03,960
What do you know?

202
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,080
Simp.

203
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,080
The more you simp, the more you get.

204
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,960
Chu, what are you doing?

205
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,240
You don't have to learn that fast.

206
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:19,360
I'm downstairs. Come down.

207
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,640
Like I need to copy you.

208
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,640
Simp.

209
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,240
I'm telling you...

210
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,480
I'm telling you right now...

211
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:32,920
Simp.

212
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,640
You can't handle love at all.

213
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,680
- Simp. - Says the guy with a room full of posters.

214
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,840
You're the real simp.

215
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,080
Simp.

216
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,280
Simp!

217
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:56,180
[Chengdu Inspiration · World Taste]

218
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,080
Ms. Chu, where are you taking me?

219
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,640
Less talking. Get in the car.

220
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:39,720
♪When clouds sink into the deep sea♪

221
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,000
♪Ripples spread♪

222
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:46,080
♪Traces of a racing heart♪

223
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:49,560
♪Is it the sky or its reflection♪

224
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:53,040
♪I can't tell anymore♪

225
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:57,360
♪Lost in your eyes♪

226
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:02,880
♪As we draw closer♪

227
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:06,040
♪The space of an embrace♪

228
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:09,240
♪Scatters the dark♪

229
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:13,520
♪When the wind comes, raise the sails♪

230
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,800
♪And sail on♪

231
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:21,360
♪Miles ahead are no longer a dream♪

232
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:27,240
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

233
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:33,040
♪Then I can spread my wings and fly with courage♪

234
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:38,800
♪If storms rise, I'll follow your light♪

235
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:44,640
♪Trusting we'll reach a warm shore♪

236
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:50,400
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

237
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:56,880
♪I'll break through the haze and run toward what I once longed for♪

238
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:01,920
♪Even if I'm hurt, I won't wander alone♪

239
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:06,320
♪You're where my heart belongs♪

240
